Kingdom: Do not delete the first row(headers)
Leave taxonid column blank if the entry is new. The database will automatically assign an ID to the entry when it's entered
To edit an existing entry in the database, put the OLD entry's id assigned by the database in this excel sheet's taxonid column then put all the new info on the corresponding columns
If there's no attribute for an entry, leave the excel's sheet column for that corresponding attribute blank
there are 86 columns for Darwin Core + 8 additional custom columns = 94 total columns(column CP)
to upload pictures: put the filename of the entries' pictures filename at speciespic column then copy the picture to C:/wamp/www/mbg/uploads/
